# VulnForge - code ownership + review routing.
#
# Lines use the standard CODEOWNERS syntax. Last matching pattern wins.
# GitHub auto-requests a review from the listed owners on any PR that
# touches matching paths.
#
# Until other maintainers are onboarded, everything routes to the project
# maintainer. Add additional entries above the catch-all when that changes.

# Catch-all - everything in the repo.
*                                       @AsafMeizner

# Security-sensitive code - tighter review expected.
/server/auth/                           @AsafMeizner
/server/sync/                           @AsafMeizner
/server/workers/                        @AsafMeizner
/server/deployment/                     @AsafMeizner
/Dockerfile.server                      @AsafMeizner
/scripts/install-server.*               @AsafMeizner
/.github/                               @AsafMeizner

# Docs changes that may affect operators - surface them prominently.
/docs/operator/                         @AsafMeizner
/docs/security/                         @AsafMeizner
